Vice President Kamala Harris addressed a teleconference with Caribbean nations to discuss strengthening partnerships and addressing common challenges. Harris emphasized the importance of the United States' relationship with the Caribbean and proposed making the meeting an annual event. The three key areas of focus for discussion were economic recovery, security, and climate and energy. Harris highlighted the United States' commitment to supporting the Caribbean in these areas and expressed the need for collaboration in addressing shared concerns. The meeting also included discussions on reducing violence in the region, combating drug and gun trafficking, and promoting climate resilience and clean energy. Harris thanked the participants for their attendance and looked forward to further discussions at the Summit of the Americas in June.